news.title: What a Holcim exit would mean for ACC, Ambuja investors & cement sector
news.para: Holcim in 2021 announced ‘Strategy 2025’ where it articulated its target to expand Solutions & Products to 30 per cent of group net sales from 8 per cent in 2020 and 15 per cent in 2021. It is also aiming to grow aggregates and ready-mix business by 2025, but the cement division.

news.title: Indiabulls Real Estate to use Rs 865 crore QIP proceeds for land acquisition, debt reduction
news.para: In a regulatory filing, Indiabulls Real Estate Ltd (IBREL) said it has completed a capital raise of Rs 865 crore at Rs 101.10 per equity share through QIP. Trading of these shares commenced on Monday on NSE and BSE.

news.title: MYRE Capital plans raise Rs 500 crore Alternative Investment Fund by July
news.para: The fund will be investing Grade A completed commercial real estate properties leased by blue chip tenants for long term along with a healthy mix of select under construction properties.

news.title: Nagpur: Operator continues to mix building debris with garbage
news.para: As the agencies are paid according per metric tonne garbage lifted, this is causing loss of public money on a daily basis. Moreover, the operator has also continued to dump garbage at an undeveloped garbage transfer station leading to soil and water pollution.

news.title: Gopikishan Damani sells 10 lakh shares of India Cements in Q4
news.para: Damani held 2,52,16,496 shares or 8.14 per cent stake in the company as of March 30, 2022, as against 2,62,16,496 equity shares or 8.46 per cent holding in the preceding quarter.

news.title: Societies in Pune wait for property tax rebates on EV charging stations
news.para: After the urban development department put out a notification last August, many housing societies have decided to have these common charging points, but members want further clarity on the percentage of rebates to be passed on to individual flat owners, federation members said.

news.title: Jamshedpur: 25 families in East Singhbhum get houses under PMAY
news.para: Now, the lives of these beneficiaries would change for the better with pucca houses, electricity and gas connections, and concrete approach roads connecting the houses to the main road.

news.title: Haryana: Soon, individual electricity connections to every flat in housing societies
news.para: In 2013, a single point-connection was made mandatory by the Haryana Electricity Regulatory Commission (HERC) for every housing society. Under this, the discom provided one connection for the entire society, which is then branched out into separate connections by the builder or the RWA.

news.title: Polycab India buys office space in Mumbai's Dadar for Rs 202 crore
news.para: The company’s newly acquired office spread over 55,400 sq ft space is in close proximity to its existing headquarters Polycab House in central Mumbai’s Mahim locality.

news.title: RBI looking for at least 50,000 sq ft office space in BKC
news.para: According to an Expression of Interest (EoI) floated by the RBI, the acquisition of office premises is proposed on a long-term lease basis for a minimum 40,000 square feet carpet area located in and around BKC within a radius of 5 km from its BKC office.

news.title: TDR scam: Land owner points fingers at Nagpur city survey officials
news.para: The probe had revealed irregularities by the urban land ceiling (ULC) department, NMC and Nagpur Improvement Trust (NIT) in issuance of transferable development rights (TDR) worth over Rs40 crore to Bharat Patel and Sanjay Avchat.

news.title: Chandigarh adviser seeks report on land pooling policy on April 19
news.para: The administration has already decided to come out with a draft on the policy being prepared by Bengaluru-based Indian Institute of Human Settlement (IIHS).

news.title: Vijayawada: Delay in property tax generation lands new house owners in soup
news.para: The state government brought a CV system instead of an annual rental value system (ARV) in property and vacant land tax calculations.

news.title: RMZ set to acquire large land parcel in Gurugram
news.para: With many under-construction projects, RMZCorp plans to make 5-6 million sq ft operational this year and is also looking at launching at least 15-20 msf by the end of this year, spread across all cities.

news.title: Haryana: DTCP releases draft guidelines on structural safety of buildings
news.para: The changes the government proposes to bring include two layers of independent checks before the occupation certificate (OC) is issued.
